00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:12.566
 according to their value from the smallest to the largest. 

00:00:12.566 --> 00:00:14.200
 And we are given these three expressions - 

00:00:14.200 --> 00:00:17.267
 q minus n, n and n minus q, 

00:00:17.267 --> 00:00:19.534
 and n and q are then applied to the numerical axis. 

00:00:19.534 --> 00:00:20.467
 In order to get better, 

00:00:20.467 --> 00:00:23.100
 let's see three divisions to the left of 0 

00:00:23.100 --> 00:00:23.900
 are minus 3. 

00:00:23.900 --> 00:00:26.900
 For each division, we must move to a lower value to the left by 1. 

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:29.733
 This must be minus 1, minus 2, 

00:00:29.733 --> 00:00:31.066
 and this is minus 3. 

00:00:31.066 --> 00:00:32.600
 Then, as we move to the right, 

00:00:32.600 --> 00:00:34.366
 each division should increase by 1. 

00:00:34.366 --> 00:00:37.867
 We have 0, 1, 2 and then 3. 

00:00:37.867 --> 00:00:39.933
 And then it just helps us to get a little better. 

00:00:39.933 --> 00:00:42.633
 But let's just look at each of these expressions. 

00:00:42.633 --> 00:00:44.967
 The first is q minus n. 

00:00:44.967 --> 00:00:47.433
 A q is to the right of n on the numerical axis. 

00:00:47.433 --> 00:00:51.300
 We know that q is greater than n. 

00:00:51.300 --> 00:00:54.367
 So if q is greater than n and subtract n from q, 

00:00:54.367 --> 00:00:56.629
 it does not really matter if both are negative 

00:00:56.629 --> 00:00:58.900
 or positive, or one is negative and the other positive. 

00:00:58.900 --> 00:01:03.833
 Simply the fact that we know q is greater than n 

00:01:03.833 --> 00:01:08.033
 means that q minus n will be positive. 

00:01:08.033 --> 00:01:09.873
 And if we actually mean that 

00:01:09.873 --> 00:01:14.366
 a specific case, q is positive, and n is negative. 

00:01:14.366 --> 00:01:16.233
 If you take a negative, 

00:01:16.233 --> 00:01:19.433
 in essence, you will add positively. 

00:01:19.433 --> 00:01:21.266
 So the value here 

00:01:21.266 --> 00:01:22.866
 not only will it be positive, 

00:01:22.866 --> 00:01:26.433
 but will be a positive value greater than q. 

00:01:26.433 --> 00:01:27.800
 And if we have to compare it with q, 

00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:29.400
 we will know that it is larger than q, 

00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:31.233
 but we do not want this. 

00:01:31.233 --> 00:01:33.033
 Now we have n. 

00:01:33.033 --> 00:01:36.800
 n is a negative value. 

00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:37.867
 It is a negative number. 

00:01:37.867 --> 00:01:39.433
 And it is a negative number between minus 1 

00:01:39.433 --> 00:01:40.233
 and minus 2. 

00:01:40.233 --> 00:01:44.600
