00:01:46.700 --> 00:01:49.300
 this thing is minus and looks like 

00:01:49.300 --> 00:01:53.066
 approximately minus 1.8. 

00:01:53.066 --> 00:01:55.233
 But how much is n minus q? 

00:01:55.233 --> 00:01:57.466
 n minus q? 

00:01:57.466 --> 00:02:01.400
 It will be the negative of q minus n. 

00:02:01.400 --> 00:02:04.067
 n minus q, we have the smaller number 

00:02:04.067 --> 00:02:08.400
 and we extract the larger number from it. 

00:02:08.400 --> 00:02:11.800
 Then this thing here will be negative. 

00:02:11.800 --> 00:02:13.769
 Therefore, the largest of these values ​​will definitely be 

00:02:13.769 --> 00:02:15.900
 q minus n, which will be positive. 

00:02:15.900 --> 00:02:18.766
 And then we have to find out which one will be smaller. 

00:02:18.766 --> 00:02:23.300
 This value n or this value n minus q? 

00:02:23.300 --> 00:02:24.766
 Let's think a little. 

